{\scaps0\caps0\cf17\expnd0\expndtw0\f5\fs24\i0\b0\par}\pard\plain \s16\sl276\slmult1\sb0\sa140\intbl\ql\widctlpar\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0\ltrpar{\scaps0\caps0\cf17\expnd0\expndtw0\f5\fs24\i0\b0
I'd also like to explain again why I want to hold lessons outside of the platform. The Preply commission is extremely high. I'm missing at least $200 a month to make ends meet if I only teach on Preply, and I can only survive if I teach a lot of students each day. Every additional student I teach means time I don't have to properly focus on each individual student. I like to prepare my lessons and sit down afterward to summarize and structure them properly. And this is only possible for me if I earn enough money, so I don't have to fill my schedule with other students. Furthermore, lessons outside the platform offer additional advantages for both me and you. Lesson times can be arranged more flexibly. I can reschedule lessons more easily and freely determine their length and I sometimes offer free lessons. Often, especially at the beginning, 50 minutes isn't necessary, as the mind is already fatigued after about 30 minutes. On Preply we are always stuck in the 50 minutes time window. Off platform the payment can be structured accordingly. Outside of Preply, I can, albeit not a large one, offer a discount,. We can make lessons longer or shorter depending on the needs and mood. This is why I've decided to offer all my students the option of taking lessons outside of Preply from now on. A good relationship with my students is paramount to me. I'm happy to extend my lessons by a few minutes without charging for the extra time. This is only possible if I don't have to teach another student immediately afterward because I depend on the income}
{\scaps0\caps0\cf17\expnd0\expndtw0\f5\fs24\i0\b0\par}\pard\plain \s16\sl276\slmult1\sb0\sa140\intbl\ql\widctlpar\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0\ltrpar{\scaps0\caps0\cf17\expnd0\expndtw0\f5\fs24\i0\b0
